{
  "stem": "4361.8",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Or it's a-- a prayer for the dead.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's not the Kaddish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's [SPEAKING HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He said, we saw the flames and your father also said, [SPEAKING HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I think today, it would be called a nervous breakdown.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I think that's when I let go, and for about two weeks, I just didn't want to go out of the house, nothing, nothing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [SIGHS] And then, I thought that my brothers would come back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I heard the following story, that my younger brother, Alex, was indeed hiding in Budapest but that he was-- one day, he went out, and he was recognized by one of his schoolmates by the name of [?",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Strimbay, ?] who sported a huge swastika and who was part of the Arrow-- Arrowhead, which was the Hungarian Nazi party, and recognized my brother and said, Fischman, what are you doing here?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Come.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my brother said to him, look, we sat next to each other in class.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Turn your head, and I'll disappear.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, he took him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was told that in February of 1945, when my brother was caught, at that time, it was known by then that the Hungarians just massacred the Jews and threw them in-- into the Danube and that-- and corpses were floating, floating for days, and that this is where my brother Alex found his end.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then, I began inquiring about my older brother, what happened to him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That I was told and that was confirmed, he worked at the [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Buna ?] factory.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when the Russians were approaching Auschwitz, just around the middle of January, they were liquidating the camp and trying to do away with-- with the evidence of genocide.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
